  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to report suspicious transactions to designated authorities. Specific requirements can vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve:\n\n1. Mandatory reporting to financial intelligence units\n2. Identifying and documenting suspicious financial activities\n3. Implementing anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n4. Conducting customer due diligence\n5. Maintaining transaction records\n6. Training employees to recognize potential money laundering indicators\n\nThe specific details and enforcement can differ between countries.",
